WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:05.839
Captioning funded by CBS
and FORD.
We go further, so you can.

00:06.673 --> 00:11.244
>> Wertheim: ON THIS SPECIAL
EDITION OF "60 MINUTES
PRESENTS:" THE RITCHIE BOYS.
THINK YOU KNOW ALL ABOUT WORLD

00:11.311 --> 00:18.318
WAR II'S GREATEST HEROES?
(<i> EXPLOSION</i> )
THINK AGAIN.
TONIGHT, YOU'LL MEET FOUR

00:18.385 --> 00:26.760
SURVIVING MEMBERS OF A SECRET
GROUP CALLED THE RITCHIE BOYS--
11,000 AMERICAN SOLDIERS, MANY
OF THEM JEWS, WHO HAD FLED NAZI

00:26.826 --> 00:32.565
GERMANY AND WERE TRAINED IN
ESPIONAGE AND PSYCHOLOGICAL
WARFARE.
HOW EFFECTIVE WERE THEY AT

00:32.632 --> 00:38.772
GATHERING INTELLIGENCE?
>> THEY WERE INCREDIBLY
EFFECTIVE.
60%-PLUS OF THE ACTIONABLE

00:38.838 --> 00:46.880
INTELLIGENCE GATHERED ON THE
BATTLEFIELD WAS GATHERED BY
RITCHIE BOYS.
THEY MADE A MASSIVE CONTRIBUTION

00:46.946 --> 01:00.560
TO ESSENTIALLY EVERY BATTLE THAT
THE AMERICANS FOUGHT-- THE
ENTIRE SETS OF BATTLES ON THE
WESTERN FRONT.

01:00.627 --> 01:05.865
>> Wertheirm: GOOD EVENING.
I'M JON WERTHEIM.
WELCOME TO "60 MINUTES
PRESENTS."

01:05.932 --> 01:12.138
FOR AS CASUALLY AS WE OFTEN TOSS
AROUND THE WORD "HERO,"
SOMETIMES, NO LESSER TERM
APPLIES.

01:12.205 --> 01:17.877
TONIGHT, WE'LL INTRODUCE YOU TO
MEMBERS OF A SECRET AMERICAN
INTELLIGENCE UNIT WHO FOUGHT IN
WORLD WAR II.

01:17.944 --> 01:25.185
WHAT'S MOST EXTRAORDINARY ABOUT
THIS GROUP?
MANY OF THEM WERE GERMAN-BORN
JEWS WHO FLED THEIR HOMELAND,

01:25.251 --> 01:30.423
CAME TO AMERICA, AND THEN JOINED
THE U.S. ARMY.
THEIR MISSION: TO USE THEIR
KNOWLEDGE OF THE GERMAN LANGUAGE

01:30.490 --> 01:37.864
AND CULTURE TO RETURN TO EUROPE
AND FIGHT NAZISM.
THE RITCHIE BOYS, AS THEY WERE
KNOWN, TRAINED IN ESPIONAGE AND

01:37.931 --> 01:44.737
FRONTLINE INTERROGATION.
AND, INCREDIBLY, THEY WERE
RESPONSIBLE FOR MOST OF THE
COMBAT INTELLIGENCE GATHERED ON

01:44.804 --> 01:49.843
THE WESTERN FRONT.
FOR DECADES, THEY DIDN'T DISCUSS
THEIR WORK.
FORTUNATELY, SOME OF THE RITCHIE

01:49.909 --> 01:57.717
BOYS ARE STILL AROUND TO TELL
THEIR TALES, AND THAT INCLUDES
THE LIFE-FORCE THAT IS GUY
STERN, AGE 99.

01:57.784 --> 02:07.460
YOU WORK SIX DAYS A WEEK, YOU
SWIM EVERY MORNING, YOU LECTURE.
ANY SIGNS OF SLOWING DOWN?
>> Guy Stern: WELL, I THINK NOT.

02:07.527 --> 02:15.768
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )
BUT I DON'T RUN AS FAST, I DON'T
SWIM AS FAST.
BUT I FEEL HAPPY WITH MY TASKS.

02:15.835 --> 02:25.311
>> Wertheim: JUST TWO WEEKS SHY
OF TURNING 100, GUY STERN DRIPS
WITH VITALITY.
HE STILL WORKS SIX DAYS A WEEK--

02:25.378 --> 02:31.784
AND IF YOU GET UP EARLY ENOUGH,
YOU MIGHT CATCH HIM WORKING OUT
AT HIS LOCAL PARK IN THE DETROIT
SUBURBS.

02:31.851 --> 02:37.924
BUT, ASK HIM ABOUT HIS MOST
FORMATIVE EXPERIENCE, AND HE
DOESN'T HESITATE.
IT WAS HIS SERVICE IN THE

02:37.991 --> 02:45.732
MILITARY DURING WORLD WAR II.
WHAT WAS IT LIKE FOR YOU,
LEAVING NAZI GERMANY, ESCAPING
AS A JEW, AND THE NEXT TIME YOU

02:45.798 --> 02:51.771
GO BACK TO EUROPE, IT'S TO FIGHT
THOSE GUYS?
WHAT WAS THAT LIKE?
>> Stern: I WAS A SOLDIER, DOING

02:51.838 --> 03:01.981
MY JOB, AND THAT PRECLUDED ANY
CONCERN THAT I WAS GOING BACK TO
A COUNTRY I ONCE WAS VERY
ATTACHED TO.

03:02.048 --> 03:09.856
I HAD A WAR TO FIGHT, AND I DID
IT.
>> Wertheim: THIS IS GUY STERN
80 YEARS AGO.

03:09.923 --> 03:17.764
HE IS AMONG THE LAST SURVIVING
RITCHIE BOYS-- A GROUP OF YOUNG
MEN, MANY OF THEM GERMAN JEWS,
WHO PLAYED AN OUTSIZED ROLE IN

03:17.830 --> 03:22.201
HELPING THE ALLIES WIN WORLD WAR
II.
THEY TOOK THEIR NAME FROM THE
PLACE THEY TRAINED: CAMP

03:22.268 --> 03:29.976
RITCHIE, MARYLAND, A SECRET
AMERICAN MILITARY INTELLIGENCE
CENTER DURING THE WAR.
STARTING IN 1942, MORE THAN

03:30.043 --> 03:37.984
11,000 SOLDIERS WENT THROUGH THE
RIGOROUS TRAINING AT WHAT WAS
THE ARMY'S FIRST CENTRALIZED
SCHOOL FOR INTELLIGENCE AND

03:38.051 --> 03:44.090
PSYCHOLOGICAL WARFARE.
>> David Frey: THE PURPOSE OF
THE FACILITY WAS TO TRAIN
INTERROGATORS.

03:44.157 --> 03:49.963
THAT WAS THE BIGGEST WEAKNESS
THAT THE ARMY RECOGNIZED THAT IT
HAD, WHICH WAS BATTLEFIELD
INTELLIGENCE, AND THE

03:50.029 --> 03:58.104
INTERROGATION NEEDED TO TALK TO,
SOMETIMES CIVILIANS, MOST OF THE
TIME PRISONERS OF WAR, IN ORDER
TO GLEAN INFORMATION FROM THEM.

03:58.171 --> 04:06.045
>> Wertheim: DAVID FREY IS A
PROFESSOR OF HISTORY AND
DIRECTOR OF THE CENTER FOR
HOLOCAUST STUDIES AT THE U.S.

04:06.112 --> 04:12.018
MILITARY ACADEMY AT WEST POINT.
HOW EFFECTIVE WERE THEY AT
GATHERING INTELLIGENCE?
>> Frey: THEY WERE INCREDIBLY

04:12.085 --> 04:19.692
EFFECTIVE.
60%-PLUS OF THE ACTIONABLE
INTELLIGENCE GATHERED ON THE
BATTLEFIELD WAS GATHERED BY

04:19.759 --> 04:24.998
RITCHIE BOYS.
>> Wertheim: 60% OF THE
ACTIONABLE INTELLIGENCE?
>> Frey: YES.

04:25.064 --> 04:31.871
THEY MADE A MASSIVE CONTRIBUTION
TO ESSENTIALLY EVERY BATTLE THAT
THE AMERICANS FOUGHT.
THE ENTIRE SETS OF BATTLES ON

04:31.938 --> 04:37.443
THE WESTERN FRONT.
>> Wertheim: RECRUITS WERE
CHOSEN BASED ON THEIR KNOWLEDGE
OF EUROPEAN LANGUAGE AND

04:37.510 --> 04:42.048
CULTURE, AS WELL AS THEIR HIGH
I.Q.s.
ESSENTIALLY, THEY WERE
INTELLECTUALS.

04:42.115 --> 04:50.056
THE LARGEST SET OF GRADUATES
WERE 2,000 GERMAN-BORN JEWS.
>> Frey: IF WE TAKE CAMP RITCHIE
IN MICROCOSM, IT WAS ALMOST THE

04:50.123 --> 04:56.396
IDEAL OF AN AMERICAN MELTING
POT.
YOU HAD PEOPLE COMING FROM ALL
OVER, UNITING FOR A PARTICULAR

04:56.462 --> 05:00.433
CAUSE.
>> Wertheim: ALL IN SERVICE OF
WINNING THE WAR?
>> Frey: ALL IN SERVICE OF

05:00.500 --> 05:05.204
WINNING THE WAR.
AND THERE'S NOTHING THAT FORGES
UNITY BETTER THAN HAVING A
COMMON ENEMY.

05:05.271 --> 05:10.143
YOU HAD A WHOLE LOAD OF
IMMIGRANTS WHO REALLY WANTED TO
GET BACK INTO THE FIGHT.
>> Wertheim: IMMIGRANTS LIKE GUY

05:10.209 --> 05:18.117
STERN.
HE GREW UP IN A CLOSE-KNIT
FAMILY IN THE TOWN OF
HILDESHEIM, GERMANY.

05:18.184 --> 05:26.125
WHEN HITLER TOOK POWER IN 1933,
STERN SAYS THE CLIMATE GREW
INCREASINGLY HOSTILE.
>> Stern: MY FELLOW STUDENTS--

05:26.192 --> 05:32.999
IT WAS AN ALL-MALE SCHOOL--
WITHDREW FROM YOU.
>> Wertheim: BECAUSE YOU WERE
JEWISH, YOU WERE OSTRACIZED?

05:33.066 --> 05:42.108
>> Stern: THAT IS CORRECT.
I WENT TO MY FATHER ONE DAY AND
I SAID, "CLASSES ARE BECOMING A
TORTURE CHAMBER."

05:42.175 --> 05:50.116
>> Wertheim: BY 1937, VIOLENCE
AGAINST JEWS WAS ESCALATING.
SENSING DANGER, STERN'S FATHER
TRIED TO GET THE FAMILY OUT--

05:50.183 --> 05:57.390
BUT THE STERNS COULD ONLY SEND
ONE OF THEIR OWN TO THE U.S.
THEY CHOSE THEIR ELDEST SON.
DO YOU REMEMBER SAYING GOODBYE

05:57.457 --> 06:02.195
TO YOUR FAMILY?
>> Stern: YES.
>> Wertheim: WHAT DO YOU
REMEMBER FROM THAT?

06:02.261 --> 06:10.369
>> Stern: HANDKERCHIEFS.
I COULDN'T KNOW AT THAT POINT
THAT I WOULD NEVER SEE MY
SIBLINGS OR MY PARENTS AGAIN,

06:10.436 --> 06:18.177
NOR MY GRANDMOTHER, AND SO FORTH
AND SO ON.
>> Wertheim: GUY STERN ARRIVED
IN THE U.S. ALONE AT AGE 15,

06:18.244 --> 06:27.987
SETTLING WITH AN UNCLE IN ST.
LOUIS.
WHEN THE JAPANESE BOMBED PEARL
HARBOR IN 1941, STERN, BY THEN A

06:28.054 --> 06:37.764
COLLEGE STUDENT, RACED TO
ENLIST.
>> Stern: I HAD AN IMMEDIATE,
VISCERAL RESPONSE TO THAT, AND

06:37.830 --> 06:46.072
THAT WAS, THIS IS MY WAR FOR
MANY REASONS.
PERSONAL, OF COURSE, BUT ALSO
THIS COUNTRY-- I WAS REALLY

06:46.139 --> 06:54.180
TREATED WELL.
>> Wertheim: IN NEW YORK, PAUL
FAIRBROOK HAD A SIMILAR IMPULSE.
NOW 98, FAIRBROOK IS THE FORMER

06:54.247 --> 07:01.788
DEAN OF THE CULINARY INSTITUTE
OF AMERICA.
HIS JEWISH FAMILY LEFT GERMANY
IN 1933 WHEN HE WAS 10.

07:01.854 --> 07:06.626
WHY DID YOU WANT TO ENLIST,
INITIALLY?
>> Paul Fairbrook: LOOK, I'M A
GERMAN JEW, AND THERE'S NOTHING

07:06.692 --> 07:14.233
THAT I WANTED MORE, IS TO GET
SOME REVENGE ON HITLER, WHO
KILLED MY UNCLES, AND MY AUNTS,
AND MY COUSINS.

07:14.300 --> 07:20.606
AND THERE WAS NO QUESTION IN MY
MIND, AND NEITHER OF ALL THE MEN
IN CAMP RITCHIE.
SO MANY OF THEM WERE JEWISH.

07:20.673 --> 07:26.245
WE WERE ALL ON THE SAME
WAVELENGTH.
WE WERE DELIGHTED TO GET A
CHANCE TO DO SOMETHING FOR THE

07:26.312 --> 07:30.650
UNITED STATES.
>> Wertheim: AT THE TIME,
THOUGH, THE MILITARY WOULDN'T
TAKE VOLUNTEERS WHO WEREN'T BORN

07:30.716 --> 07:38.257
IN THE U.S.
BUT, WITHIN A FEW MONTHS, THE
GOVERNMENT REALIZED THESE SO-
CALLED ENEMY ALIENS COULD BE A

07:38.324 --> 07:44.330
VALUABLE RESOURCE IN THE WAR.
WHY WERE THE RITCHIE BOYS SO
SUCCESSFUL?
>> Fairbrook: WELL, BECAUSE IT

07:44.397 --> 07:50.102
WAS AN UNUSUAL PART OF THE
UNITED STATES ARMY.
YOU CAN LEARN TO SHOOT A RIFLE
IN SIX MONTHS, BUT YOU CAN'T

07:50.169 --> 07:54.240
LEARN FLUENT GERMAN IN SIX
MONTHS.
AND THAT'S WHAT THE KEY TO THE
SUCCESS WAS.

07:54.307 --> 08:00.413
>> Wertheirm: WAS IT YOUR
KNOWLEDGE OF THE LANGUAGE OR
YOUR KNOWLEDGE OF THE PSYCHOLOGY
AND THE GERMAN CULTURE?

08:00.479 --> 08:06.319
>> Fairbrook: OH, THAT IS A VERY
GOOD QUESTION.
THAT IS THE KEY TO BEING A GOOD
INTERROGATOR.

08:06.385 --> 08:14.327
YOU REALLY KNOW AN AWFUL LOT OF
THE SUBTLETIES WHEN YOU'RE
HAVING A CONVERSATION WITH
ANOTHER GERMAN, AND WE WERE ABLE

08:14.393 --> 08:22.201
TO FIND OUT THINGS IN THEIR
ANSWERS THAT ENABLED US TO ASK
MORE QUESTIONS.
YOU REALLY HAVE TO UNDERSTAND,

08:22.268 --> 08:30.309
IT HELPS TO HAVE BEEN BORN IN
GERMANY IN ORDER TO-- IN ORDER
TO DO A GOOD JOB.
>> Wertheim: BOTH REFUGEES LIKE

08:30.376 --> 08:37.817
FAIRBROOK AND STERN, AS WELL AS
A NUMBER OF AMERICAN-BORN
RECRUITS WITH REQUISITE LANGUAGE
SKILLS, WERE DRAFTED INTO THE

08:37.884 --> 08:45.424
ARMY AND SENT TO CAMP RITCHIE.
HOW DID YOU FIND OUT YOU WERE
GOING TO GO TO CAMP RITCHIE?
>> Stern: I WAS CALLED TO THE

08:45.491 --> 08:52.198
COMPANY OFFICE AND TOLD, "YOU'RE
SHIPPING OUT."
AND I SAID, "MAY I KNOW WHERE
I'M GOING?"

08:52.265 --> 08:57.336
AND HE SAID "NO, MILITARY
SECRET."
>> Wertheim: THEY SWORE YOU TO
SECRECY?

08:57.403 --> 09:02.808
>> Stern: YES
>> Wertheim: ORIGINALLY A
RESORT, CAMP RITCHIE WAS A
CURIOUSLY IDYLLIC SETTING TO

09:02.875 --> 09:10.283
PREPARE FOR THE HARSHNESS AND
BRUTALITY OF WAR.
NESTLED IN THE BLUE RIDGE
MOUNTAINS OF MARYLAND, IT WAS

09:10.349 --> 09:16.255
AWAY FROM PRYING EYES-- AND
PRYING SPIES- BUT CLOSE ENOUGH
TO DECISION MAKERS AT THE
PENTAGON.

09:16.322 --> 09:22.261
GIVE US A SENSE OF THE KINDS OF
COURSES THEY TOOK.
>> Frey: WELL, THE MOST
IMPORTANT PART OF THE TRAINING

09:22.328 --> 09:28.267
WAS THAT THEY LEARNED TO DO
INTERROGATION, AND IN PARTICULAR
OF PRISONERS OF WAR.
TECHNIQUES WHERE YOU WANT TO GET

09:28.334 --> 09:34.040
PEOPLE TO TALK TO YOU.
YOU WANT TO CONVINCE THEM THAT
YOU'RE TRUSTWORTHY.
YOU WANT TO GIVE THEM THAT

09:34.106 --> 09:38.377
FEELING THAT YOU KNOW WHO THEY
ARE, THEY KNOW WHO YOU ARE.
YOU KNOW A LOT ABOUT THEM
ALREADY.

09:38.444 --> 09:46.652
SO, WHATEVER INFORMATION THEY'RE
GIVING YOU IS INFORMATION THAT
YOU PROBABLY ALREADY KNOW.
BUT THEY ALSO DID TERRAIN

09:46.719 --> 09:54.160
ANALYSIS, THEY ALSO DID PHOTO
ANALYSIS, AND AERIAL
RECONNAISSANCE ANALYSIS.
THEY DID COUNTERINTELLIGENCE

09:54.226 --> 09:58.264
TRAINING.
>> Wertheim: THIS WAS REALLY A
BROAD RANGE OF INTELLIGENCE
ACTIVITIES.

09:58.331 --> 10:04.270
>> Frey: IT WAS A VERY BROAD
RANGE AND THEY DID IT ALL
GENERALLY IN EIGHT WEEKS.
>> Wertheim: WHAT YOU DESCRIBE,

10:04.337 --> 10:10.276
IT ALMOST SOUNDS LIKE THESE WERE
PRECURSORS TO C.I.A. AGENTS.
>> Frey: THEY WERE, IN FACT.
SOME OF THEM WERE TRAINED AS

10:10.343 --> 10:16.282
SPIES AND SOME OF THEM WENT ON
TO CAREERS AS SPIES.
>> Victor Brombert: MY PARENTS
WERE PACIFISTS, SO THE IDEA OF

10:16.349 --> 10:26.359
MY GOING TO WAR WAS FOR THEM
CALAMITOUS, HOWEVER THEY
REALIZED THAT IT WAS A NECESSARY
WAR, ESPECIALLY FOR US.

10:26.425 --> 10:33.132
>> Wertheim: VICTOR BROMBERT,
NOW 98-YEARS-OLD, IS A FORMER
PROFESSOR OF ROMANCE LANGUAGES
AND LITERATURE AT YALE, AND THEN

10:33.199 --> 10:38.471
PRINCETON.
HE WAS BORN IN BERLIN TO A
RUSSIAN JEWISH FAMILY.
WHEN HITLER CAME TO POWER, THE

10:38.537 --> 10:46.278
BROMBERTS FLED TO FRANCE, AND
THEN TO THE U.S.
EAGER TO FIGHT THE NAZIS, HE,
TOO, JOINED THE ARMY.

10:46.345 --> 10:52.818
AFTER RECRUITERS FOUND OUT HE
SPOKE FOUR LANGUAGES, THEY
DISPATCHED HIM TO CAMP RITCHIE,
WHERE STRENUOUS CLASSROOM

10:52.885 --> 11:02.762
INSTRUCTION WAS COUPLED WITH
STRENUOUS FIELD EXERCISES.
>> Brombert: THERE WERE LONG AND
DEMANDING EXERCISES AND CLOSE

11:02.828 --> 11:10.336
COMBAT TRAINING.
"HOW TO KILL A SENTRY FROM
BEHIND."
I THOUGHT, "I'M NEVER GOING TO

11:10.403 --> 11:14.874
DO THAT," BUT I WAS SHOWN HOW TO
DO IT.
>> Wertheim: SO PHYSICAL COMBAT
TRAINING AS WELL AS

11:14.940 --> 11:18.811
INTELLIGENCE?
>> Brombert: YES, WELL, WITH A
STICK.
YOU SORT OF SWING IT AROUND THE

11:18.878 --> 11:26.218
NECK FROM BEHIND AND THEN PULL.
>> Wertheim: AMONG THE UNUSUAL
SIGHTS AT RITCHIE: A TEAM OF
U.S. SOLDIERS DRESSED IN GERMAN

11:26.285 --> 11:32.525
UNIFORMS.
THE RITCHIE BOYS TRAINED FOR WAR
AGAINST THESE FAKE GERMANS WITH
FAKE GERMAN TANKS MADE OUT OF

11:32.591 --> 11:40.199
WOOD.
ANOTHER UNUSUAL SIGHT: TOWERING
OVER RECRUITS, FRANK LEAVITT, A
WORLD WAR I VETERAN AND PRO

11:40.266 --> 11:46.338
WRESTLING STAR AT THE TIME, WAS
AMONG THE INSTRUCTORS.
TRAINING WAS DESIGNED TO BE AS
REALISTIC AS POSSIBLE.

11:46.405 --> 11:52.912
THE RITCHIE BOYS PRACTICED
STREET FIGHTING IN LIFE-SIZE
REPLICAS OF GERMAN VILLAGES, AND
QUESTIONED MOCK CIVILIANS IN

11:52.978 --> 12:01.020
FULL SCALE GERMAN HOMES.
SOME OF THE PRISONERS WERE
ACTUAL GERMAN P.O.W.s BROUGHT TO
CAMP RITCHIE SO THE RITCHIE BOYS

12:01.087 --> 12:06.459
COULD PRACTICE THEIR
INTERROGATION TECHNIQUES.
I UNDERSTAND YOU, YOU HAD
SPARRING PARTNERS.

12:06.525 --> 12:13.966
YOU PLAYACTED--
>> Brombert: ONE HAD TO PLAYACT
WITH SOME OF THE PEOPLE WERE
ACTING AS PRISONERS AND SOME OF

12:14.033 --> 12:20.873
THEM WERE REAL PRISONERS.
>> Wertheim: BY THE SPRING OF
1944, THE RITCHIE BOYS WERE
READY TO RETURN TO WESTERN

12:20.940 --> 12:28.414
EUROPE, THIS TIME AS NATURALIZED
AMERICANS IN AMERICAN UNIFORMS.
STILL, IF THEY WERE CAPTURED,
THEY KNEW WHAT THE NAZIS WOULD

12:28.481 --> 12:37.089
DO TO THEM.
SOME OF THEM REQUESTED NEW DOG
TAGS, WITH VERY GOOD REASON.
THIS DOG TAG SAYS HEBREW.

12:37.156 --> 12:42.528
DID YOUR DOG TAG IDENTIFY YOU AS
JEWISH?
>> Stern: I PREFERRED NOT HAVING
IT.

12:42.595 --> 12:46.632
I ASKED THEM TO LEAVE IT OFF
>> Wertheim: YOU DIDN'T WANT TO
BE IDENTIFIED AS JEWISH GOING
BACK TO WESTERN EUROPE.

12:46.699 --> 12:58.410
>> Stern: NO BECAUSE I KNEW THAT
THE CONTACT WITH GERMANS MIGHT
NOT BE VERY NICE.
>> Wertheim: ON JUNE 6, 1944, D-

12:58.477 --> 13:06.585
DAY, THE ALLIES LAUNCHED ONE OF
THE MOST SWEEPING MILITARY
OPERATIONS IN HISTORY.
A MIGHTY ONSLAUGHT OF MORE THAN

13:06.652 --> 13:18.564
160,000 MEN, 13,000 AIRCRAFT,
AND 5,000 VESSELS.
>> Stern: WE WERE ON A P.T. BOAT
TAKING OFF FROM SOUTHAMPTON.

13:18.631 --> 13:26.572
AND WE ALL WERE SCARED.
WE WERE BRIEFED THAT THE GERMANS
WERE NOT GOING TO WELCOME US
GREATLY.

13:26.639 --> 13:34.480
AS A JEW, I KNEW I MIGHT NOT BE
TREATED EXACTLY BY THE GENEVA
RULES.
>> Wertheim: DIVIDED INTO SIX-

13:34.547 --> 13:40.486
MAN TEAMS, THE RITCHIE BOYS WERE
ATTACHED TO DIFFERENT ARMY
UNITS.
THEIR JOB: TO PROVIDE

13:40.553 --> 13:46.692
BATTLEFIELD INTELLIGENCE.
WHEN THEY LANDED ON THE BEACHES
OF NORMANDY, WEHRMACHT TROOPS
WERE WAITING FOR THEM, WELL-

13:46.759 --> 13:54.567
ARMED AND WELL PREPARED.
VICTOR BROMBERT WAS WITH THE
FIRST AMERICAN ARMORED DIVISION
TO LAND ON OMAHA BEACH.

13:54.633 --> 14:02.007
HE IS STILL HAUNTED BY WHAT HE
EXPERIENCED THAT DAY.
>> Brombert: I SAW IMMENSE
DEBRIS.

14:02.074 --> 14:10.382
WOUNDED PEOPLE.
DEAD PEOPLE.
I REMEMBER BEING UP ON A CLIFF
THE FIRST NIGHT OVER OMAHA

14:10.449 --> 14:18.657
BEACH.
AND WE WERE STRAFED AND I SAID
TO MYSELF, UH, "NOW, IT'S THE
END," BECAUSE I COULD- YOU COULD

14:18.724 --> 14:25.998
FEEL THE MACHINE GUN BULLETS.
>> Wertheim: IS THAT WHEN YOU
FIRST REALIZE- I'M- I'M IN A WAR
HERE?

14:26.065 --> 14:33.973
>> Brombert: YES, I REALIZED
THAT I WAS AFRAID.
I NEVER CALCULATED THAT THERE IS
SUCH A THING AS TERROR, FEAR.

14:34.039 --> 14:40.179
SO, I EXPERIENCED VISCERALLY,
FEAR.
>> Wertheim: ON THE FRONT LINES
FROM NORMANDY ONWARDS, THE

14:40.246 --> 14:46.185
RITCHIE BOYS FOUGHT IN EVERY
MAJOR BATTLE IN EUROPE,
COLLECTING TACTICAL
INTELLIGENCE, INTERROGATING

14:46.252 --> 14:52.524
PRISONERS AND CIVILIANS, ALL IN
SERVICE OF WINNING THE WAR.
WHEN WE COME BACK, WE'LL HEAR
ABOUT SOME OF THE SURPRISING

14:52.591 --> 15:03.002
WAYS THEY FORGED CONNECTIONS
WITH THE ENEMY IN ORDER TO
EXTRACT STRATEGIC INFORMATION.

15:04.903 --> 15:12.311
>> Wertheim: IN 1944, THE
RITCHIE BOYS HEADED TO EUROPE TO
FIGHT IN A WAR THAT WAS FOR
THEM, INTENSELY PERSONAL.

15:12.378 --> 15:18.917
THEY WERE MEMBERS OF A SECRET
GROUP WHOSE MASTERY OF THE
GERMAN LANGUAGE AND CULTURE
HELPED THEM PROVIDE BATTLEFIELD

15:18.984 --> 15:26.191
INTELLIGENCE THAT PROVED PIVOTAL
TO THE ALLIES' VICTORY.
THE RITCHIE BOYS LANDED ON THE
BEACHES OF NORMANDY ON D-DAY,

15:26.258 --> 15:31.063
AND HELPED LIBERATE PARIS.
THEY CROSSED INTO GERMANY WITH
THE ALLIED ARMIES AND WITNESSED
THE HORRORS OF THE NAZI

15:31.130 --> 15:38.304
CONCENTRATION CAMPS.
ALL THE WHILE, THEY TRACKED DOWN
EVIDENCE AND INTERROGATED NAZI
CRIMINALS, LATER TRIED AT

15:38.370 --> 15:46.812
NUREMBERG.
IT WAS ALSO IN EUROPE THAT SOME
OF THEM, LIKE GUY STERN, LEARNED
WHAT HAD HAPPENED TO THE

15:46.879 --> 15:51.083
FAMILIES THEY LEFT BEHIND.
>><i> THIS IS IT.</i>
<i>THEY'RE ON THE BEACH.</i>
>> Wertheim: BY THE SUMMER OF

15:51.150 --> 15:58.424
1944, GERMAN TROOPS IN NORMANDY
WERE OUTNUMBERED AND
OVERPOWERED.
THE ALLIES LIBERATED PARIS IN

15:58.490 --> 16:04.463
AUGUST.
>><i> THE DATE WAS AUGUST 25.</i>
>> Wertheim: AND DROVE NAZI
TROOPS OUT OF FRANCE.

16:04.530 --> 16:10.903
BUT HITLER WAS DETERMINED TO
CONTINUE THE WAR.
IN THE ARDENNES REGION OF
BELGIUM, THE GERMANS MOUNTED A

16:10.969 --> 16:16.909
MASSIVE COUNTEROFFENSIVE, WHICH
