THE BULGE."
I SEE A TENT IN THE BACKGROUND

16:16.975 --> 16:21.847
OF THAT PHOTO RIGHT IN FRONT OF
YOU.
>> Stern: YES, THAT'S MY
INTERROGATION TENT.

16:21.914 --> 16:25.718
>> Wertheim: SO, THIS IS YOU ON
THE JOB.
YOU'RE IN BELGIUM?
>> Stern: YES, DOING MY JOB

16:25.784 --> 16:30.989
INTERROGATING.
RIGHT.
>> Wertheim: AMID THE CHAOS OF
WAR, GUY STERN AND THE OTHER

16:31.056 --> 16:38.964
RITCHIE BOYS HAD A JOB TO DO.
EMBEDDED IN EVERY ARMY UNIT,
THEY INTERROGATED TENS OF
THOUSANDS OF CAPTURED NAZI

16:39.031 --> 16:46.872
SOLDIERS AS WELL AS CIVILIANS,
EXTRACTING KEY STRATEGIC
INFORMATION ON ENEMY STRENGTH,
TROOP MOVEMENTS, AND DEFENSIVE

16:46.939 --> 16:52.878
POSITIONS.
THEY THEN TYPED UP THEIR DAILY
REPORTS IN THE FIELD TO BE
PASSED UP THE CHAIN OF COMMAND.

16:52.945 --> 17:03.055
>> Brombert: OUR INTERROGATIONS,
IT HAD TO DO WITH TACTICAL
IMMEDIATE CONCERNS.
AND THAT'S WHY CIVILIANS COULD

17:03.122 --> 17:10.262
BE USEFUL AND SOLDIERS COULD BE
USEFUL.
"WHERE IS THE MINEFIELD?"
VERY IMPORTANT BECAUSE YOU SAVE

17:10.329 --> 17:16.935
LIFE IF YOU KNOW WHERE THE MINE.
"WHERE IS THE MACHINE GUN NEST?"
"HOW MANY MACHINE GUNS DO YOU
HAVE THERE?"

17:17.002 --> 17:23.208
"WHERE ARE YOUR RESERVE UNITS?"
AND IF YOU DON'T GET IT FROM ONE
PRISONER, YOU MIGHT GET IT FROM
THE OTHER.

17:23.275 --> 17:30.716
>> Wertheim: 98-YEAR-OLD VICTOR
BROMBERT SAYS THEY RELIED ON
THIR CAMP RITCHIE TRAINING TO
GET PEOPLE TO OPEN UP.

17:30.783 --> 17:38.490
>> Brombert: WE IMPROVISED
ACCORDING TO THE SITUATION,
ACCORDING TO THE KIND OF UNIT,
ACCORDING TO THE KIND OF PERSON

17:38.557 --> 17:46.965
WE WERE INTERROGATING.
BUT CERTAINLY WHAT DID NOT WORK
WAS VIOLENCE OR THREAT OF
VIOLENCE.

17:47.032 --> 17:53.839
NEVER.
WHAT DID WORK IS COMPLICITY.
>> Wertheim: WHAT-- WHAT DO YOU
MEAN?

17:53.906 --> 17:58.477
>> Brombert: BY COMPLICITY I
MEAN, "OH, WE ARE TOGETHER IN
THIS WAR.
YOU ON ONE SIDE AND WE ON THIS

17:58.544 --> 18:05.050
SIDE.
ISN'T IT A MISERABLE THING?
AREN'T WE ALL, SORT OF, TIRED OF
IT?"

18:05.117 --> 18:09.621
>> Wertheim: THE SHARED
EXPERIENCE?
>> Brombert: THE SHARED
EXPERIENCE, EXACTLY.

18:09.688 --> 18:17.029
GIVING OUT SOME CIGARETTES ALSO
HELPS A LOT.
A FRIENDLY APPROACH.
TRYING TO BE HUMAN.

18:17.095 --> 18:23.035
>> Wertheim: THE RITCHIE BOYS
CONNECTED WITH PRISONERS ON
SUBJECTS AS VARIED AS FOOD AND
SOCCER RIVALRIES, BUT THEY

18:23.101 --> 18:29.575
WEREN'T ABOVE USING DECEPTION ON
DIFFICULT TARGETS.
THE RITCHIE BOYS DISCOVERED THAT
THE NAZIS WERE TERRIFIED OF

18:29.641 --> 18:38.250
ENDING UP IN RUSSIAN CAPTIVITY,
AND THEY USED THAT TO GREAT
EFFECT.
IF A GERMAN P.O.W. WOULDN'T

18:38.317 --> 18:47.593
TALK, HE MIGHT FACE GUY STERN
DRESSED UP AS A RUSSIAN OFFICER.
>> Stern: I HAD MY WHOLE UNIFORM
WITH MEDALS, RUSSIAN MEDALS, AND

18:47.659 --> 18:55.100
I GAVE MYSELF THE NAME
"COMMISSAR KRUKOV."
>> Wertheim: THAT'S WHAT YOU
CALLED YOURSELF?

18:55.167 --> 19:00.706
>> Stern: THAT WAS MY PSEUDONYM.
>> Wertheim: HOW DID YOU DO
COMMISSAR?
>> Stern: THANK YOU FOR ASKING.

19:00.772 --> 19:11.116
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )
I GAVE MYSELF ALL THE
ACCOUTERMENTS OF LOOKING LIKE A
FIERCE RUSSIAN COMMISSAR.

19:11.183 --> 19:23.095
AND SOME WE DIDN'T BREAK, BUT
80% WERE SO DARNED SCARED OF THE
RUSSIANS AND WHAT THEY WOULD DO.
>> Wertheim: SO, THERE'S A REAL

19:23.161 --> 19:33.372
ELEMENT OF COSTUMES AND
DECEPTION AND ACCENTS.
>> Stern: YES, AND IT'S
THEATRICS IN A WAY, YES.

19:33.438 --> 19:39.177
>> Wertheim: THEIR SUBJECTS
RANGED FROM LOW LEVEL GERMAN
SOLDIERS TO HIGH RANKING NAZI
OFFICERS, INCLUDING HANS

19:39.244 --> 19:47.119
GOEBBELS, BROTHER OF HITLER'S
CHIEF PROPOGANDIST, JOSEPH
GOEBBELS.
ANOTHER BIT OF INDISPENSABLE

19:47.185 --> 19:55.193
RITCHIE BOY HANDIWORK: THE ORDER
OF BATTLE OF THE GERMAN ARMY.
PAUL FAIRBROOK HELPED WRITE THIS
COMPACT MANUAL, KNOWN AS "THE

19:55.260 --> 20:03.168
RED BOOK," WHICH OUTLINED IN
GREAT DETAIL THE MAKEUP OF
VIRTUALLY EVERY NAZI UNIT,
INFORMATION EVERY RITCHIE BOY

20:03.235 --> 20:07.506
COMMITTED TO MEMORY.
>> Fairbrook: WHEN THE SOLDIERS
SAID, "I'M NOT GOING TO TALK,"
THEY COULD SAY, "WAIT A MINUTE.

20:07.573 --> 20:13.712
I KNOW ALL ABOUT YOU.
LOOK, I GOT A BOOK HERE AND IT
TELLS ME THAT YOU WERE HERE AND
YOU WENT THERE AND YOUR BOSS WAS

20:13.779 --> 20:17.316
THIS."
AND THEY WERE IMPRESSED WITH
THAT
>> Wertheim: SO, IT SOUNDS LIKE

20:17.382 --> 20:25.157
THIS GAVE THE OFFICERS IN THE
FIELD A GUIDE TO THE GERMAN ARMY
SO THEY COULD THEN INTERROGATE
THE GERMAN P.O.W.s MORE

20:25.223 --> 20:29.094
EFFICIENTLY.
>> Fairbrook: THAT'S EXACTLY
RIGHT.
>> Wertheim: THE RITCHIE BOYS

20:29.161 --> 20:37.869
EARNED A REPUTATION FOR
DELIVERING IMPORTANT TACTICAL
INFORMATION FAST, MAKING A MAJOR
CONTRIBUTION TO EVERY BATTLE ON

20:37.936 --> 20:43.175
THE WESTERN FRONT.
>> Frey: THE WORK THEY DO IN THE
FIELD, BEING ABLE TO GLEAN
INFORMATION SIMPLY BY, FROM THE

20:43.241 --> 20:51.450
UNIFORM THAT A CAPTURED P.O.W.
IS WEARING OR THE TYPE OF WEAPON
THAT THEY HAVE OR THE UNIT THAT
THEY'VE JUST CAPTURED.

20:51.516 --> 20:59.324
THAT INFORMATION IS OF CRITICAL
IMPORTANCE BECAUSE IT TELLS YOU
WHERE CERTAIN UNITS ARE, AND IF
YOU KNOW WHERE CERTAIN UNITS

20:59.391 --> 21:05.163
ARE, YOU KNOW WHERE THE WEAK
SPOTS ARE.
YOU KNOW WHERE THE STRONG POINTS
ARE, AND YOU KNOW YOU WHAT TO

21:05.230 --> 21:11.803
AVOID AND WHAT TO ATTACK.
>> Wertheim: DAVID FREY TEACHES
HISTORY TO CADETS AT THE U.S.
MILITARY ACADEMY AT WEST POINT.

21:11.870 --> 21:18.276
>> Frey: THIS IS WHERE THE
HAVING AN INTELLIGENCE OFFICER
FROM CAMP RITCHIE WAS OF
CRITICAL IMPORTANCE, BECAUSE

21:18.343 --> 21:23.181
THEY WOULD KNOW THIS
INFORMATION.
YOUR AVERAGE COMMANDER IN THE
FIELD MIGHT NOT.

21:23.248 --> 21:29.187
>> Wertheim: THEIR WORK SAVED
LIVES?
>> Frey: ABSOLUTELY.
THEY CERTAINLY SAVED LIVES.

21:29.254 --> 21:35.527
I THINK THAT'S QUANTIFIABLE.
PART OF WHAT THE RITCHIE BOYS
DID WAS TO CONVINCE GERMAN UNITS
TO SURRENDER WITHOUT FIGHTING.

21:35.594 --> 21:39.264
>> Wertheim: AND YOU'RE SAYING
THAT SOME OF THAT ORIGINATED AT
CAMP RITCHIE?
>> Frey: MUCH OF IT ORIGINATED

21:39.331 --> 21:45.103
AT CAMP RITCHIE BECAUSE IT HAD
NEVER- IT HADN'T BEEN DONE
BEFORE.
HOW DO YOU APPEAL TO PEOPLE IN

21:45.170 --> 21:51.109
THEIR OWN LANGUAGE?
KNOWING HOW TO SHAPE THAT APPEAL
WAS PRETTY CRITICAL TO THE
SUCCESS OF THE MOBILE BROADCAST

21:51.176 --> 21:57.382
UNITS.
>> Wertheim: IN TRUCKS EQUIPPED
WITH LOUDSPEAKERS, RITCHIE BOYS
WENT TO THE FRONT LINES UNDER

21:57.449 --> 22:04.990
HEAVY FIRE, AND TRIED, IN
GERMAN, TO PERSUADE THEIR NAZI
COUNTERPARTS TO SURRENDER.
