22:05.057 --> 22:10.262
LEAFLETS FROM AIRPLANES BEHIND
ENEMY LINES.
>> Wertheim: THIS WAS ONE OF THE
LEAFLETS THAT WAS DROPPED OUT.

22:10.328 --> 22:19.304
>> Stern: OUT OF A PLANE.
I HAVE SOME THAT WERE SHOT.
THIS ONE WAS OUR MOST EFFECTIVE
LEAFLET.

22:19.371 --> 22:29.247
AND WHY WAS THAT?
BECAUSE EISENHOWER HAD SIGNED IT
AND THE GERMANS HAD AN
INCREDIBLY NAIÃVE APPROACH TO

22:29.314 --> 22:36.621
EVERYTHING THAT WAS SIGNED AND
SEALED.
>> Wertheim: AND YOU THINK
BECAUSE IT HAD THAT SIGNATURE,

22:36.688 --> 22:43.295
SOMEHOW THAT CERTIFIED IT.
>> Stern: YES, THAT CARRIED
WEIGHT, AND THE BELIEF IN THE
PRINTED MATTER WAS VERY GREAT.

22:43.361 --> 22:47.399
>> Wertheim: THAT'S THE KIND OF
THING YOU WOULD KNOW.
>> Stern: YES.
>> Wertheim: AS A FORMER GERMAN

22:47.466 --> 22:52.838
WHO UNDERSTOOD THE PSYCHOLOGY
AND THE MENTALITY.
>> Stern: THAT'S CORRECT.
>> Wertheim: APART FROM THE

22:52.904 --> 22:58.310
FIGHTING, THERE WERE OTHER
THREATS CONFRONTING THE RITCHIE
BOYS.
GIVEN THEIR FOREIGN ACCENTS,

22:58.376 --> 23:03.615
THEY WERE IN PARTICULAR DANGER
OF BEING MISTAKEN FOR THE ENEMY
BY THEIR OWN TROOPS, WHO
INSTITUTED PASSWORDS AT

23:03.682 --> 23:10.122
CHECKPOINTS.
>> Brombert: WHAT HAPPENED TO
ONE OF THE RITCHIE BOYS-- AT
NIGHT ON THE WAY TO THE LATRINE,

23:10.188 --> 23:14.526
HE WAS ASKED FOR A PASSWORD AND
HE GAVE THE NAME, THE WORD FOR
THE PASSWORD, BUT WITH A GERMAN
ACCENT.

23:14.593 --> 23:18.697
HE WAS SHOT RIGHT AWAY AND
KILLED.
>> Wertheim: DID YOU EVER WORRY
YOUR ACCENT MIGHT GET YOU

23:18.764 --> 23:26.705
KILLED?
>> Brombert: YES, OF COURSE.
YOU KNOW, I DON'T TALK LIKE AN
ALABAMA PERSON OR A TEXAN.

23:26.772 --> 23:31.977
>> Wertheim: SOME RITCHIE BOYS
WERE RECRUITED TO GO ON SECRET
MISSIONS DURING THE WAR.
97-YEAR-OLD MAX LERNER, AN

23:32.043 --> 23:39.384
AUSTRIAN JEW FLUENT IN GERMAN
