AGENT WITH THE
COUNTERINTELLIGENCE CORPS,

23:39.451 --> 23:46.091
PASSING INFORMATION TO FRENCH
UNDERGROUND RESISTANCE GROUPS.
YOU WERE TRAINED AS A SPY?
>> Max Lerner: YES.

23:46.158 --> 23:53.165
>> Wertheim: WHAT WERE YOU
TRAINED TO DO?
>> Lerner: WEAR CIVILIAN
CLOTHES, PASS MESSAGES, KILL.

23:53.231 --> 23:59.337
>> Wertheim: THIS IS GOING
BEHIND ENEMY LINES.
I MEAN, THIS IS YOU'RE TAKING
YOUR LIFE IN YOUR HANDS HERE.

23:59.404 --> 24:05.410
>> Lerner: WELL, IT WAS A WAR.
>> Wertheim: THAT'S HOW YOU
LOOKED AT IT.
>> Lerner: IT WAS MY WAR.

24:05.477 --> 24:13.185
AND I NEEDED TO GET MY OWN BACK.
I WANTED DESPERATELY TO DO
SOMETHING.
>> Wertheim: AT ONE POINT, MAX

24:13.251 --> 24:19.457
LERNER DISGUISED HIMSELF AS A
GERMAN OFFICER AND SNUCK BEHIND
ENEMY LINES, LEADING A TEAM OF
AMERICAN SOLDIERS INTO A GERMAN

24:19.524 --> 24:26.298
DEPOT AT NIGHT AND DESTROYING
THE EQUIPMENT.
DID YOU WORRY WHAT MIGHT HAPPEN
IF YOU WERE CAPTURED?

24:26.364 --> 24:29.768
>> Lerner: I WASN'T SMART
ENOUGH.
>> Wertheim: WHAT DO YOU SUSPECT
MIGHT HAVE HAPPENED?

24:29.835 --> 24:35.407
>> Lerner: OH, I WOULD HAVE BEEN
KILLED.
>> Wertheim: BY THE SPRING OF
1945, ALLIED FORCES NEARED

24:35.473 --> 24:42.714
BERLIN AND HITLER TOOK HIS LIFE
IN HIS UNDERGROUND BUNKER.
GERMANY SURRENDERED ON MAY 8 OF
THAT YEAR.

24:42.781 --> 24:50.589
WHAT DO YOU REMEMBER FEELING
THAT DAY?
>> Stern: ELATED.
IT WAS ABSOLUTELY, "WE WON,

24:50.655 --> 24:55.460
KID!"
(.LAUGHS )
>> Wertheim: AND THOSE ARE YOUR,
THOSE ARE YOUR COMRADES?

24:55.527 --> 24:59.364
>> Stern: YES.
>> Wertheim: THOSE ARE YOUR
GUYS.
>> Stern: YES.

24:59.431 --> 25:07.505
>> Wertheim: BUT JOY TURNED TO
HORROR AS ALLIED SOLDIERS AND
THE WORLD LEARNED THE FULL SCALE
OF THE NAZI MASS EXTERMINATION.

25:07.572 --> 25:15.480
GUY STERN RECALLS ARRIVING AT
BUCHENWALD CONCENTRATION CAMP
THREE DAYS AFTER ITS LIBERATION,
ALONGSIDE A FELLOW AMERICAN

25:15.547 --> 25:26.024
SERGEANT.
>> Stern: WE WERE WALKING ALONG
AND YOU SAW THESE EMACIATED,
HORRIBLY LOOKING, CLOSE TO DEATH

25:26.091 --> 25:37.569
PEOPLE.
AND SO, I FELL BACK BEHIND,
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT TO BE SEEN
CRYING TO A HARDENED SOLDIER,

25:37.636 --> 25:51.516
AND THEN HE LOOKED AROUND TO
LOOK WHERE I WAS, HOW I WAS
DELAYED, AND HE, THIS GOOD
FELLOW FROM MIDDLE OF OHIO, WAS

25:51.583 --> 25:59.457
BAWLING JUST AS I WAS.
>> Wertheim: A FEW DAYS LATER,
STERN RETURNED TO THE PLACE OF
HIS BIRTH, HOPING TO REUNITE

25:59.524 --> 26:07.565
WITH HIS FAMILY.
BUT HILDESHEIM WAS NOW IN RUINS.
A CHILDHOOD FRIEND DESCRIBED TO
STERN HOW HIS PARENTS, YOUNGER

26:07.632 --> 26:15.340
BROTHER AND SISTER HAD BEEN
FORCED FROM THEIR HOME AND
DEPORTED.
>> Stern: THEY WERE KILLED

26:15.407 --> 26:23.415
EITHER IN WARSAW OR IN
AUSCHWITZ.
NONE OF MY FAMILY SURVIVED.
I WAS THE ONLY ONE TO GET OUT.

26:23.481 --> 26:29.521
>> Wertheim: DID YOU EVER ASK
YOURSELF, "WHY ME?"
WHY WERE YOU THE ONE THAT MADE
IT TO THE UNITED STATES?

26:29.587 --> 26:43.568
>> Stern: YES, EVEN LAST NIGHT.
