CALLED "FINAL SOLUTION" TO KILL
ALL EUROPEAN JEWS.
MAX LERNER RECALLS THAT IN ONE
RESPECT AT LEAST, IDENTIFYING

33:00.178 --> 33:08.186
MOST S.S. MEMBERS WAS EASY.
>> Lerner: YOU KNOW HOW TO TELL
AN S.S. MAN?
>> Wertheim: HOW?

33:08.252 --> 33:15.593
>> Lerner: THEY HAVE A TATTOO OF
THEIR BLOOD GROUP UNDER THEIR
LEFT ARMS.
>> Wertheim: S.S. MEN, YOU'RE

33:15.660 --> 33:20.198
SAYING, HAVE A TATTOO UNDER
THEIR LEFT ARM WITH THEIR BLOOD
TYPE?
>> Lerner: YES.

33:20.264 --> 33:27.105
OR THEY HAD AN EFFORT TO ERASE
IT.
>> Wertheim: THE PURPOSE OF THE
TATTOO WAS TO IDENTIFY A

33:27.171 --> 33:35.480
SOLDIER'S BLOOD TYPE IN CASE A
TRANSFUSION WAS NEEDED OR IF HIS
DOG TAGS WENT MISSING.
MAX LERNER RECALLS BEING PUT IN

33:35.546 --> 33:42.153
CHARGE OF ONE PROMINENT CAPTURED
GERMAN PRISONER AT A JAIL IN
WEISBADEN, GERMANY.
THAT WAS JULIUS STREICHER, THE

33:42.220 --> 33:48.226
FOUNDER AND EDITOR OF THE NAZI
PAPER "DER STUERMER" AND ONE OF
THE COUNTRY'S LEADING ANTI-
SEMITES.

33:48.292 --> 33:55.099
>> Lerner: HE SPENT SEVERAL DAYS
IN MY JAIL.
AND I MADE SURE HE KNEW THAT IT
WAS A JEW WHO CONTROLLED HIM.

33:55.166 --> 34:03.708
>> Wertheim: YOU LET HIM KNOW
YOU WERE JEWISH?
>> Lerner: OH, YES.
>> Wertheim: STRIECHER WAS LATER

34:03.775 --> 34:11.048
TRIED AND CONVICTED AT THE
INTERNATIONAL MILITARY TRIBUNAL
AT NUREMBERG, WHERE
CONCENTRATION CAMP SURVIVORS WHO

34:11.115 --> 34:16.554
BORE WITNESS TO THE MASS MURDER
FACED DOWN THEIR NAZI
TORMENTORS.
DOZENS OF RITCHIE BOYS WORKED AT

34:16.621 --> 34:23.394
THE NUREMBERG TRIALS AS
PROSECUTORS, INTERROGATORS AND
TRANSLATORS.
RITCHIE BOYS ALSO COLLECTED

34:23.461 --> 34:30.234
EVIDENCE WHICH LED TO THE
PROSECUTION OF MANY HIGH RANKING
NAZIS INCLUDING HERMANN GOERING,
HEAD OF THE LUFTWAFFE; RUDOLPH

34:30.301 --> 34:39.844
HESS, DEPUTY FURHER TO ADOLF
HITLER; AND WILHELM KEITEL,
CHIEF OF THE WEHRMACHT,
GERMANY'S ARMED FORCES.

34:39.911 --> 34:47.084
>><i> THE EVIDENCE RELATING TO WAR</i>
<i>CRIMES HAS BEEN OVERWHELMING IN</i>
<i>ITS VOLUME AND ITS DETAIL.</i>
>> Wertheim: ALL WERE CONVICTED

34:47.151 --> 34:52.356
FOR THEIR CRIMES, AND MANY WERE
EXECUTED.
AFTER THE WAR, GUY STERN AND THE
OTHER RITCHIE BOYS WERE

34:52.423 --> 35:00.665
CELEBRATED FOR THEIR
ACHIEVEMENTS.
>> Stern: THE BRONZE STAR WAS
GIVEN TO ME RIGHT AT THE END OF

35:00.731 --> 35:06.304
HOSTILITIES.
THIS IS THE GOOD CONDUCT MEDAL,
WHICH I'M NOT REALLY ENTITLED
TO.

35:06.370 --> 35:18.316
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )
AND THIS HERE IS THE EUROPEAN
THEATRE OF OPERATIONS MEDAL WITH
FIVE BATTLES IN WHICH I

35:18.382 --> 35:23.221
PARTICIPATED.
>> Wertheim: DO YOU CONSIDER
YOURSELF A HERO?
>> Stern: GOD, NO.

35:23.287 --> 35:40.638
I TELL YOU, WHEN WE LANDED ON
OMAHA BEACH, THERE WERE THE
WHOLE HEIGHTS HAD BEEN OCCUPIED
BY THE GERMAN ARTILLERY.

35:40.705 --> 35:52.316
AND I LOOKED UP ON THOSE HEIGHTS
AND THERE WERE OUR AMERICAN
SOLDIERS IN FULL OCCUPATION ON
THE DAY-D PLUS THREE, AND I SAID

35:52.383 --> 36:06.364
TO MYSELF, "THAT CAN'T BE DONE."
AND TO TAKE THOSE HEIGHTS
AGAINST HEAVY FIRING, GOING UP
THOSE STEEP CLIFFS, AND OF

36:06.430 --> 36:15.406
COURSE, IT HAD BEEN DONE.
THE EVIDENCE WAS BEFORE US.
THOSE WERE THE HEROES.
>> Wertheim: GUY STERN RETURNED

36:15.473 --> 36:24.382
TO NORMANDY IN 2016 TO PAY HIS
RESPECTS TO THE MORE THAN 9,300
MEN BURIED IN THE AMERICAN
CEMETERY THERE, ON THE BLUFF

36:24.448 --> 36:32.390
OVERLOOKING THE HALLOWED BEACH.
DID THE RITCHIE BOYS REDEFINE
WHAT IT MEANS TO BE A SOLDIER
AND CONTRIBUTE TO A MILITARY?

36:32.456 --> 36:36.827
>> Frey: I THINK THEY DID.
BECAUSE THEY SERVED IN SO MANY
DIFFERENT CAPACITIES.
>> Wertheim: HISTORY PROFESSOR

36:36.894 --> 36:44.402
DAVID FREY RUNS THE CENTER FOR
HOLOCAUST AND GENOCIDE STUDIES
AT THE U.S. MILITARY ACADEMY AT
WEST POINT.

36:44.468 --> 36:52.376
>> Frey: THERE WERE RITCHIE BOYS
THAT WERE IN THE FIRST WAVE ON
THE FIRST DAY AT D-DAY.
THERE WERE RITCHIE BOYS WHO WERE

36:52.443 --> 36:58.516
IN P.O.W. CAMPS EMBEDDED AND
GATHERING INFORMATION IN THE
UNITED STATES.
SOME DIDN'T EVEN GO OVER TO- TO

36:58.583 --> 37:04.455
EUROPE.
THERE WERE RITCHIE BOYS WHO WERE
IN VIRTUALLY EVERY BATTLE THAT
YOU CAN THINK OF, AND SOME

37:04.522 --> 37:09.493
ACTUALLY SUFFERED THE WORST
FATE.
THERE WERE TWO WHO WERE ACTUALLY
CAPTURED AT THE BATTLE OF THE

37:09.560 --> 37:15.066
BULGE.
AND WHEN THEIR IDENTITY WAS
DISCOVERED, THEY WERE SUMMARILY
EXECUTED BY THE GERMANS THAT HAD

37:15.132 --> 37:18.202
CAPTURED THEM.
>> Wertheim: BECAUSE THEY WERE
JEWISH?
>> Frey: BECAUSE THEY WERE

37:18.269 --> 37:24.442
JEWISH.
>> Wertheim: WEHRMACHT CAPTAIN
CURT BRUNS, CONVICTED BY A
MILITARY TRIBUNAL OF ORDERING

37:24.508 --> 37:34.385
THE MURDER OF THOSE TWO RITCHIE
BOYS, WAS EXECUTED BY A FIRING
SQUAD IN JUNE, 1945.
AFTER THE WAR, THE RITCHIE BOYS

37:34.452 --> 37:40.458
CONTINUED THEIR WORK.
98-YEAR-OLD PAUL FAIRBROOK
HELPED SET UP THE GERMAN
MILITARY DOCUMENTS SECTION AT

37:40.524 --> 37:48.432
CAMP RITCHIE, A VAST CATALOG OF
MORE THAN 20,000 CAPTURED GERMAN
DOCUMENTS.
>> Fairbrook: THEY SENT US BACK

37:48.499 --> 37:54.438
TO CAMP RITCHIE AND THEY CREATED
SOMETHING THAT I CALL THE
EQUIVALENT OF THE LIBRARY OF
CONGRESS.

37:54.505 --> 38:00.444
WE HAD TO- WE GOT A LOT OF
GERMAN PRISONERS WHO WERE
WILLING TO HELP US CATALOG ALL
THOSE DOCUMENTS.

38:00.511 --> 38:06.717
>> Wertheim: THE PROJECT
DETAILED EVERY ASPECT OF THE
GERMAN ARMY'S OPERATIONS DURING
THE WAR, INCLUDING HOW THEY WERE

38:06.784 --> 38:14.992
STRUCTURED, HOW THEY MOBILIZED
AND HOW THEY USED INTELLIGENCE.
THE U.S. WAR DEPARTMENT USED
THIS COLLECTION OF GERMAN

38:15.059 --> 38:20.698
DOCUMENTS TO STUDY GERMANY'S
BATTLES WITH THE SOVIETS ON THE
EASTERN FRONT, IN ORDER TO BE
BETTER PREPARED FOR ANY FUTURE

38:20.765 --> 38:28.305
CONFLICT WITH RUSSIA.
>> Wertheim: SO, THERE'S ALL
SORTS OF IMPACT YEARS AND YEARS
AND YEARS AFTER THE WAR FROM

38:28.372 --> 38:32.510
THIS, THIS CAMP IN MARYLAND?
>> Frey: RIGHT.
IT WAS NOT ONLY THAT SHORT TERM
IMPACT ON THE BATTLEFIELD.

38:32.576 --> 38:39.784
IT WAS AN IMPACT ON WAR CRIMES.
THEN SHAPING THE COLD WAR ERA,
THEY REALLY PLAYED A SIGNIFICANT
ROLE.

38:39.850 --> 38:47.525
>> Wertheim: AFTER THE WAR, GUY
STERN, VICTOR BROMBERT, PAUL
FAIRBROOK AND MAX LERNER CAME
HOME, MARRIED, AND WENT TO IVY

38:47.591 --> 38:53.030
LEAGUE SCHOOLS ON THE G.I.
BILL.
GUY STERN BECAME A PROFESSOR AND
TAUGHT FOR ALMOST 50 YEARS.

38:53.097 --> 39:00.504
THEY ALL ROSE TO THE TOP OF
THEIR FIELDS, AS DID A NUMBER OF
OTHER RITCHIE BOYS.
I UNDERSTAND THERE ARE SOME

39:00.571 --> 39:05.876
RITCHIE BOYS, BECAME FAIRLY
PROMINENT FIGURES.
>> Frey: THERE ARE A WHOLE
VARIETY OF PROMINENT RITCHIE

39:05.943 --> 39:11.849
BOYS.
>> Wertheim: IT TURNS OUT THAT
AUTHOR J.D. SALINGER WAS A
RITCHIE BOY.

39:11.916 --> 39:18.556
SO WAS ARCHIBALD ROOSEVELT,
GRANDSON OF THEODORE ROOSEVELT.
AS WAS PHILANTHROPIST DAVID
ROCKEFELLER, AND MEDIA BARON AND

39:18.622 --> 39:24.562
BILLIONAIRE JOHN KLUGE.
>> Frey: SOME BECAME
AMBASSADORS.
OTHERS WERE ACTUALLY REALLY

39:24.628 --> 39:31.001
IMPORTANT IN AMERICAN SCIENCE.
>> Wertheim: AND NOTABLY,
PROFESSOR FREY SAYS, MORE THAN
250 RITCHIE BOYS CONTINUED TO

39:31.068 --> 39:38.576
WORK IN THE FIELD OF
INTELLIGENCE AFTER THE WAR,
BECOMING PROFESSIONAL SPIES.
>> Frey: MANY OF THOSE WHO

39:38.642 --> 39:47.251
TRAINED AT CAMP RITCHIE ACTUALLY
DID GO ON TO THE O.S.S., THE
PRECURSOR TO THE C.I.A., THAT
MEANT THAT THE PEOPLE WHO

39:47.318 --> 39:54.558
LEARNED THEIR CRAFT AT CAMP
RITCHIE PLAYED A SIGNIFICANT
ROLE IN SETTING UP WHAT
EVENTUALLY BECAME THE C.I.A.

39:54.625 --> 40:00.197
>> Wertheim: HOW DO YOU THINK WE
SHOULD BE RECALLING THE RITCHIE
BOYS?
>> Frey: I THINK WE LOOK AT THIS

40:00.264 --> 40:04.568
GROUP AND WE SEE TRUE HEROES.
WE SEE THOSE WHO ARE THE
GREATEST OF THE GREATEST
GENERATION.

40:04.635 --> 40:12.576
THESE ARE PEOPLE WHO MADE
MASSIVE CONTRIBUTIONS, WHO
HELPED SHAPE WHAT IT MEANT TO BE
AMERICAN AND WHO, IN SOME CASES,

40:12.643 --> 40:18.582
GAVE THEIR LIVES IN SERVICE TO
THIS COUNTRY.
>> Wertheim: THIS-- THIS IS A
REMARKABLE STORY.

40:18.649 --> 40:24.588
WHY DO SO FEW AMERICANS KNOW
ABOUT THIS?
>> Frey: BECAUSE IT INVOLVES
MILITARY INTELLIGENCE, MUCH OF

40:24.655 --> 40:34.231
IT WAS ACTUALLY KEPT SECRET
UNTIL THE, THE 1990s.
A LOT OF WHAT WAS LEARNED AND
THE METHODS USED ARE IMPORTANT

40:34.298 --> 40:40.571
TO KEEP SECRET.
AND ONLY IN THE EARLY 2000s DID
WE BEGIN TO SEE REUNIONS OF THE
RITCHIE BOYS.

40:40.638 --> 40:48.579
>> Wertheim: NOW IN THEIR LATE
90s, THESE HUMBLE WARRIORS STILL
KEEP IN TOUCH, SWAPPING STORIES
ABOUT A CHAPTER IN AMERICAN

40:48.646 --> 40:56.921
HISTORY NOW FINALLY BEING TOLD.
WHAT IS IT LIKE WHEN YOU GET
TOGETHER AND REFLECT ON THIS
EXPERIENCE GOING ON 80 YEARS

40:56.987 --> 41:03.460
AGO?
>> Stern: WE ALWAYS FIND ANOTHER
ANECDOTE TO TELL.
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )

41:03.527 --> 41:08.666
>> Wertheim: YOU HAVE A SMILE ON
YOUR FACE WHEN YOU THINK BACK.
>> Stern: YES, THIS IS WHAT
HAPPENS.

41:08.732 --> 41:16.073
>> Wertheim: IT WAS HARD FOR US
NOT TO NOTICE THAT BEYOND THE
STORIES RUNS A DEEP SENSE OF
PRIDE.

41:16.140 --> 41:20.644
>> Fairbrook: YOU BET YOUR LIFE
I'M PROUD OF THE RITCHIE BOYS.
IT WAS WONDERFUL TO BE PART OF
THEM!

41:20.711 --> 41:28.652
I WAS PROUD TO BE IN THE
AMERICAN ARMY AND WE WERE ABLE
TO DO WHAT WE HAD TO DO.
I DON'T THINK WE'RE HEROES, BUT

41:28.719 --> 41:35.860
THE OPPORTUNITY TO HELP FIGHT
AND WIN THE WAR WAS A WONDERFUL
WAY.
I CAN LOOK ANYBODY STRAIGHT IN

41:35.926 --> 41:40.664
THEIR EYE AND SAY I THINK I'VE
EARNED THE RIGHT TO BE AN
AMERICAN.
AND THAT'S WHAT, THAT'S WHAT IT

41:40.731 --> 41:46.503
DID FOR ME.
